{
	"fnNumber": "152",
	"fnHTML": "<p><em>Agape</em> is not used in the Bible only for the highest love. The love between a husband and wife is also called <em>agape</em> (Ephesians 5,28; Colossians 3,19). Sometimes the word is even used in a negative sense. You can love darkness (John 3,19), you can love honour and praise (Luke 11,43), you can love the world (1 John 2.15; 2 Timothy 10), you can have a deficient love (Luke 7,47) and your love can even grow cold (Matthew 24,12). <em>Agape</em> is used in all these cases. Throughout the Buddhist scriptures <span lang='pi'>mettā</span> is used exclusively for the highest love.</p>"
},
