	"fnNumber": "221",
	"fnHTML": "<p><span data-sesame-key='wp:Mahāvaṃsa:Geiger 1912a' class='sesame'><em>Mahāv</em>aṁsa</span> XII,21. Being a popular legend that developed several centuries after the Buddha the <span data-sesame-key='wp:Hariti' class='sesame'>Hariti</span> story is not found in the Pāḷi Tipitaka. Consequently the <span data-sesame-key='wp:Mahāvaṃsa:Geiger 1912a' class='sesame'>Mahāvaṁsa</span> version of the story attributes her conversion to the monks Sona and Uttara who lived during the time of King Asoka.</p>"
