	"fnNumber": "225",
	"fnHTML": "<p>In Japan <span data-sesame-key='wp:Kṣitigarbha' class='sesame'>Kṣitigarbha</span> is also known as Migawari Jizo, “He Who Takes Upon Himself Our Suffering.” Statues of <span data-sesame-key='wp:Kṣitigarbha' class='sesame'>Kṣitigarbha</span> sometimes depict him with scars and wounds, the result of trying to protect purgatorial beings from receiving their just punishment.</p>"
